External knowledge is not explicitly required for this query as it is more focused on the calculation of performance metrics and ranking, without any vague or metaphorical language. However, some external knowledge that could be implied includes:
- The World Cup is an international soccer tournament held every 4 years; 
- Team performance can be measured by metrics such as goals scored, goals conceded, matches played, yellow and red cards received, possession, and pass and shot accuracy; 
- A higher average goals scored and lower average goals conceded generally indicate better team performance.

sql:
SELECT year, team, goals_for, goals_against
FROM world_cup_data
WHERE team = 'Uruguay' AND year = 1930;

SELECT wc.team, wc.average_possession
FROM world_cup_data wc
WHERE wc.won > 0 AND wc.average_possession > 50;
